name: real_world_url_confusable_cyrillic
description: |
  The apparent `paypal` label uses Cyrillic U+0440, U+0430, U+0443, U+0440,
  U+0430 followed by Latin `l`. It serializes as
  `xn--l-7sba6dbr.example` and is not the paired Latin host, despite their
  visual similarity in many fonts.

  UTS #39 documents confusable and mixed-script spoofing risks:
  https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr39/
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: utf8
unicode-meta:
  code-units: 33
  code-points: 28
  scalar-values: 28
  legacy-grapheme-clusters: 28
  extended-grapheme-clusters: 28
tags:
  - "real-world"
  - "url"
  - "host"
  - "idn"
  - "unicode-confusables"
  - "mixed-script"
  - "homograph"
  - "text-spoofing"
  - "not-equal"
  - "valid"
---
https://раураl.example/login
